KW  - Transaction prices
KW  - Quote midpoints
AB  - We establish the bid–ask spread bias embedded in the Campbell et al. (2001; 2022) (CLMX) estimate of idiosyncratic variance (IV). Minimizing the bid–ask spread effect by using quote midpoints or increasing the return horizon eliminates the upward (CLMX) and downward time trend (Bekaert et al., 2012) in IV. Five natural experiments illustrate that an exogenous shock in the recording of transaction prices significantly affects the resulting time trend in IV. Cross-sectional and time-series regressions show that the bid–ask spread subsumes the CLMX IV time trend.
